post_text:
The FYPS Board met today and approved the Re-Start & Distance Learning Plan. They also approved the Health and Safety Plan. The two plans will be posted on our website as well as being included in the Student Handbook once revisions are made to both plans, as recommended by the FYPS Board.
After much discussion and deliberation, the FYPS Board also approved re-starting the school year in Phase 3, as described in the Re-Start & Distance Learning Plan. Phase 3 is the ‚ÄúVirtual/Online‚Äù Instructional Model.
This decision was based on recommendation by Standing Rock Sioux Tribe, current community trends regarding COVID-19 (North Dakota Department of Health and Standing Rock Incident Command Center)input from parents, students, and staff, as well as the health and safety of students and staff. The FYPS Board will review and assess the instructional model at each monthly board meeting. Any changes to Instructional Phases will be communicated to parents and community.

Superintendent Baker

Here is what Phase 3 looks like:

Hello all! Our staff just had a virtual staff meeting and we were talking about things that were going well and things that maybe aren‚Äôt going so well right now. We have had some families say they were having issues getting our devices connected to their WiFi. We encourage you to call your internet provider to discuss this issue with them. When your child is on line doing their classes it‚Äôs important they do not have other windows for other outside activities (streaming and games, etc) during the time they are to be on for class as it will slow every thing down.
We were also told online games such as Fortnite will slow things down as well, even if it is on a separate device.
We also want you all to know who much we miss being ‚Äúin school‚Äù and hope you are well!!!

post_text:
Dear 8th grade Class of 2020,
You might not be a high school senior, but this was a big year for you and you deserve to celebrate this ending.
We know how much you were looking forward to your 8th grade recognition, spending the last few months with your friends, finishing your last season of sports as a middle schooler and all the extra things we had planned for you!
For many parents and families, we were looking forward to seeing our child‚Äôs end of the year celebration and cross over from a middle schooler to a high schooler.
For many parents and families it may be their first child, and for some it may be their last child to leave middle school and enter into their new chapter.
We want you to know that no matter what, we are always proud and we are so hopeful that you can still experience these wonderful memories! We will do our best to celebrate you in all these ways. While we don't know what the future for the rest of the school year holds we do know this...
We love our 8th graders!!!

Since I miss you guys so much--I REALLY DO!!!! -- I'm feeling very "teacherish." So, let's see what happened on March 24 in decades gone by. Go to Factmonster.com/dayinhistory/March24 (that's tomorrow, Tuesday), and find the answers to the following questions. Anybody who participates will be rewarded (not generously, mind, but rewarded nevertheless) when we get back to school.

1. What was Queen Elizabeth I of England doing on this day, and in what year?

2. What was Elvis doing on this day, and in what year?(SHAME ON YOU IF YOU DO NOT KNOW WHO ELVIS WAS!!!---Geesh‚Ä¶.)

3. On this day in 2002, what two major milestones in America's march toward Equal Diversity were achieved?

post_text:
Sunday, March 22, 2020
Hello FYPS families and community members,
There have not been any real changes since the governor's press conference on Thursday where he announced that North Dakota Public Schools are closed until further notice.
FYPS is continuing to work on their distance learning plan that is to be submitted to the governor for approval. This plan is due Friday, March 27, 2020. Once we have further information and instructions for that we will get that out to everyone.
Tomorrow we will continue with lunch drop offs. We will also have school supplies, learning packets, and devices for those families who have notified the principal. If you are in need of a device please email Principal Kramer.
We hope you are all doing well and staying healthy!!
- FYPS Administration

post_text:
FYPS has suspended all building/facility use requests until further notice. This includes all Open Gym and Weight Room activities outside of normal school hours. This decision is being made to ensure that any and all sanitizing done by our custodial staff remains as undisturbed as possible when our students are not present.

All non-employee keys and fobs will be collected by Principal Kramer. If you have any questions you may contact Superintendent Baker.

Thank you for your support in ensuring a healthy environment for our students and staff.

post_text:
The Administration at FYPS is closely monitoring North Dakota‚Äôs and Standing Rock‚Äôs threat level of COVID-19 (Corona Virus). North Dakota is currently Low Risk - Threshold 1 means unmitigated or uncontained community transmission of coronavirus is occurring elsewhere, but there may not be evidence of significant community transmission in North Dakota yet. At this level, authorities should consider initiating minimally restrictive, or burdensome, but effective mitigation measures. Additionally, authorities should consider canceling or postponing events where a substantive number of attendees are from high-risk locations or high-risk populations.
We want to assure you that
our custodial staff is sanitizing FYMS during our spring break. We will keep you updated of any changes.

Superintendent Baker
